#Approach:

Sort Colors – Dutch National Flag Algorithm (3 Pointer Approach)

Is problem me array me sirf 0, 1 aur 2 hote hain.
Hume inhe sort karna hai without using sort function aur in-place.

Hum 3 pointers use karte hain: low, mid, high.

low ka matlab: 0s ka region
mid ka matlab: current element
high ka matlab: 2s ka region

Algorithm:
Agar nums[mid] == 0:
Swap nums[low] aur nums[mid], phir low++ aur mid++

Agar nums[mid] == 1:
Bas mid++ (kyunki 1 already correct position me hai)

Agar nums[mid] == 2:
Swap nums[mid] aur nums[high], phir high--
(mid ko yaha increment nahi karte kyunki swapped element check karna hota hai)

Is tarah array 3 parts me divide ho jata hai:
0s | 1s | 2s

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1)

#Code:

class Solution {

    private void swap(int[] nums, int start, int end){
        int temp = nums[start];
        nums[start] = nums[end];
        nums[end] = temp;
    }

    public void sortColors(int[] nums) {
        int low = 0;
        int mid = 0;
        int high = nums.length - 1;

        while (mid <= high){
            if(nums[mid] == 0){
                swap(nums, low, mid);
                low++;
                mid++;
            }
            else if(nums[mid] == 1){
                mid++;
            }
            else{
                swap(nums, mid, high);
                high--;
            }
        }
    }
}
